# Rule: .agents/RULES.md

This is the index. It must:

- one-line its mission at the top;
- have a markdown table with columns `Path glob` | `Rule file` | `Purpose`;
- list the explicit allowlist (files that need no rule);
- document the procedure for adding a new rule (4 steps);
- be kept in sync with `.agents/rules/*.md.rule` — if the table and the
  rules disagree, both fail CI (`bun run check:md` reads only the table).

## Template

```markdown
# `.agents/RULES.md` — index of rules for tracked `.md` files

> **Why this file exists.** <one paragraph>

## Rules index

| Path glob | Rule file | Purpose |
|-----------|-----------|---------|
| … | … | … |

## Allowlist (no rule required)
- …

## Adding a new rule
1. …
2. …
3. …
4. …
```